    think='Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the PR. Let me compile my
review findings.\n\n## PR Overview\nThis is PR #38 (branch feat/issue-37) fixing
a bug: "Dev Tools Drawer 的 Server URL 输入框修改后仍会自动填充默认地址".\n\n## 
Changes Made\n1. `.husky/pre-commit` - added `unset GIT_DIR`\n2. `.husky/pre-pus
h` - added flutter PATH and `unset GIT_DIR`\n3. `Makefile` - added `SHELL := /bi
n/bash`\n4. `apps/mobile/lib/core/di/di.dart` - changed `DevToolsCubit` from `re
gisterFactory` to `registerLazySingleton`\n5. `apps/mobile/lib/presentation/widg
ets/dev_tools_wrapper.dart` - changed from `BlocProvider(create: ...)` to `BlocP
rovider.value(value: _cubit)` with `_cubit` loaded in `initState`\n6. `apps/mobi
le/test/dev_tools_widget_test.dart` - added tests for the bug fix\n7. `docs/modu
les/dev-tools.md` - formatting updates and documentation of the `registerLazySin
gleton` change\n\n## Review Analysis\n\n### 1. 全链路完整性\n- This is a bug fix
PR for a mobile-only dev tool issue. The fix is appropriately scoped.\n- However
, there are some concerns:\n  - The `DevToolsWrapper` now creates `_cubit = getI
t<DevToolsCubit>()..load();` in `initState()` without any `kDebugMode` guard ins
ide the widget itself. The widget is only used inside `kDebugMode` in `app.dart`
, but if someone were to use it elsewhere without the guard, it could crash in r
elease mode since `DevToolsCubit` is only registered in `kDebugMode`.\n  - Actua
lly, looking more carefully: `DevToolsWrapper` itself doesn\'t have a `kDebugMod
e` guard, but it\'s only instantiated inside `if (kDebugMode)` in `app.dart`. Th
is was the existing pattern. The docs/modules/dev-tools.md mentions that DevTool
sWrapper should be wrapped in kDebugMode, which is done in app.dart.\n\n### 2. 
规范符合性\n- The DI change from `registerFactory` to `registerLazySingleton` ma
kes sense to preserve state across drawer open/close cycles.\n- `BlocProvider.va
lue` is correctly used instead of `BlocProvider(create: ...)`.\n- The `_cubit` l
ifecycle is managed by get_it, and the widget only provides it via `BlocProvider
.value`. This is good.\n- However, there\'s a potential memory leak issue: `DevT
